04/04/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Defence Minister Teodor Melescanu said on Thursday (April 3rd) that Romania may boost its contingent in Afghanistan by 150 troops.
At the end of a working dinner with NATO counterparts held within the organisation's summit in Bucharest, Melescanu explained the troops could oversee the training of Afghan army staff.
Earlier in the day, Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu said Bucharest might boost its troop level, if all other NATO members do.
Romania currently has 650 troops in Afghanistan.
(Cotidianul - 04/04/08;
Mediafax - 03/04/08)
